Outbreak of Mysterious Fever in Siliguri, North Bengal: RFI
-----------------------------------------------------------
SILIGURI: An undiagnosed fever raging in this commercial city of North
Bengal has claimed 4 more lives taking the death toll to 14. The 4, who
died of this undiagnosed fever on Mon 19 Feb 2001, included the resident
medical officer of a private nursing home. All the affected individuals had
complained of severe headache and drowsiness, officials said. Another 20
patients with the same symptoms have been admitted to the Siliguri
Sub-divisional Hospital, North Bengal Medical College.
An eminent cardiologist of the city, who also developed the symptoms, has
been moved to Kolkata. Health and Family Welfare Minister, Partha Dey, who
arrived here on Monday, has convened a high-level meeting.
